body.name: All-Clad HA1 Hard Anodized Nonstick Fry Pan Set 2 Piece, 8, 10 Inch Induction Oven Broiler Safe 500F, Lid Safe 350F Pots and Pans, Cookware Black
features: This cookware set includes 8 inch and 10 inch Fry Pans, ideal for browning, searing, and pan-frying foods like eggs, vegetables, and meats Its flat surface and flared side walls make it ideal for one hand sautéing and easy turning with a spatula

High Quality Performance with Everyday Convenience - HA1 Nonstick heavy gauge aluminum and stainless-steel base deliver even heat for consistent, delicious cooking. The high-quality PTFE nonstick brings a long-lasting and easy release when cooking
Design You Will Love- HA1 Nonstick has a sleek and stylish contoured design. Our double riveted stainless steel handles ensure a secure grip

Oven safe up to 500°F and compatible with any stovetop, including induction Dishwasher safe To preserve the nonstick, wash your cookware with a soap and sponge, and using silicone, nylon or wooden utensils
Designed in Canonsburg, PA - USA, Made in China
body.description: If you have something to fry, whether it’s a big catfish filet or small diced potatoes, this classic kitchen staple is the cookware to help you do it. Ideal for cooking at high heat, flipping and tossing foods is a snap, thanks to the flat base and flared sides. As part of our HA1 Nonstick collection, this Fry Pan Set is constructed of heavy gauge aluminum and its interior is engineered with 3 layers of our high performing, PFOA-free nonstick coating. This coating keeps food molecules from clinging to the surface, so it’s ideal for delicate or sticky foods. Its exterior features an anti-warp induction compatible base that makes it compatible with induction cooktops and bumps up durability. All in all, it offers professional performance and durability combined with easy food release that’s easy to clean for a convenient cooking experience. The set includes both an 8-inch pan with a petite, space-saving profile that’s perfect for quick bites and a 10-inch pan that offers plenty of room for full, filling dishes. Once you’re done eating, simply put it in the dishwasher or give it a quick hand washing to wrap up the easiest cooking experience you’ve ever had.

Sleek & Stylish Contoured Design Dark matte finish combined with prominent All-Clad stainless steel accents. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars New All Clad non-stick frypans
reviews.reviewText: So far so good. We are replacing a couple of older, well worn, 8” and 10” non-stick frypans that served us well. The weight of these is what we expect from A/C. But we haven’t tested them yet and will update this as we do.As per the handles, what the heck is the big deal! We have 30 A/C pots and pans and they all have the same handle. It has never been an issue. My wife is a lifelong professional chef and chef educator and never an issue. Until I read these reviews I had never heard a complaint.After using them for a week (my wife is a retired professional chef and is ALWAYS cooking-and we have over 30 All-Clad pans), we found them perfectly functional and a huge bargain. We have no complaints of the evil handles. They work well as all AC handles do and the NS surfaces as well. Nothing to add to the above except that they are not showing any signs of wear at all after a few months. But we take care of our pans! No overheating, no metal utensils and no scrubbing with abrasives. We like them enough that we just bought a 12” pan from this same line.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars You'll notice a difference from regular frying pans
reviews.reviewText: The best addition to my cookware. I have always used AllClad but have yet to have the frying pans. There is a big difference from your average frying pan. The pans heat slowly instead of fast, reducing the chance of burning food. I noticed the meat cooks evenly, no matter what section of the pan it is on. And the food slides off with no sticking, and these pans are super easy to clean!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great non stick pans
reviews.reviewText: So far I've been very pleased with these pans! Feel substantial and look great! I've not had any issues at all. Eggs slide right out, and SO EASY to clean!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The best non stick surface
reviews.reviewText: I am giving this product five stars. First let me say the pot handles suck. They are weird awkward and it is a terrible design. However, the surface of these nonstick pans is absolutely incredible. It is a hard surface. It is not coated with any weird chemicals and nothing sticks to it. As long as you take your time and heat slowly, I have had absolutely no problems with this. It is perfect for sautéing tofu and getting a nice crunch on the outside without using any oil I would highly recommend these pans even though the handles are awful, the most important part is the nonstick, right?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not as thick as original
reviews.reviewText: We bought a full set of this cookware several years ago. We use them every day and they are excellent. High quality. easy to clean. Look nice. But the small pan was burned and had some things stuck to it It was scraped with a metal spatula and now didn't look so good. I ordered a replacement. It came and weas the same size. Looks nice. But it is not as thick and slightly lighter weight. The metal is just a little bit thinner. I don't know if this is for all the newer ones or just what we ordered from Amazon. But being the smallest pan it's not that important

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These were better than expected.
reviews.reviewText: This is a heavy-duty pan -- almost like cast iron including the weight. They sit very flat and the nonstick is really non-stick. I have fried eggs wi.th just a brushing of oil and they slide around as if floating in oil. They are super easy to clean. Wiping with a paper towel will almost clen the pans. I find the heating the pan just higher than the cooking range for few minutes improves the evenness of heat for uniform cooking.The main negative is the handle. It is strange. It is U-shaped on top and narrows at it gets closer to pan. It is awkward. It is similar to a Cuisinart frying pan handle which has a U-shaped handle, but it widens as it gets closer to the pan which works better with your hand while holding the pan. It is also long. All Clad needs to rethink this handle design.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I like the pans, and on sale were worth the price. The sauté pan isn’t quite as large or deep as the one I’m used to. The nonstick is great, hope it lasts. I’m only using plastic on it.Update:I've been using these for a bit now and really like them. They hold the heat very well, are solid, and the non-stick remains awesome. I've upped it to five stars, since the value is great considering the sale it was on.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: They are very heavy. But it's easy to clean. Food doesn't stick. Worth the buy.

Needed a medium sized non-stick pan and found this 2 pack from a trusted brand name. This is the same set sold in William and Sonoma and the price it was listed at, at the time, it was a little bit cheaper on Amazon. Works as expected, easy to use, nothing has stuck so far. Easy to clean, I haven’t used in dishwasher and I don’t plan to even though they say it’s dishwasher safe, no need, it cleans up so easy with a soft sponge and warm water with dish soap. The larger sized pan is perfect if you’re looking to do some fried rice for one or two people, or it will cook 3-4 eggs perfectly. The smaller one is really just for cooking one or two eggs. Handle doesn’t heat up when cooking. A solid purchase, would buy again.

reviews.reviewTitle: Great pans at a reasonable price
reviews.reviewText: These are made by one of the best Mfg in the business. They non stick and work well with even heat on my induction range.

reviews.reviewTitle: AMAZING PANS! BUT PAN LITS LACK STEAM VENTS
reviews.reviewText: These non-stick All-Clad pans are AMAZING, so far. We were able to make omelettes, sunny-side-up eggs, pierogis on them, without any food sticking to the pan. The cleanup is a breeze. We're very happy with the pans so far, and will try to make them last as long as possible by using only silicone utensils and soft dish-washing sponges on them. The only thing I don't like is that the pan lids don't have any steam vents. Luckily, I kept my glass Copper Chef pan lids, which do have steam vents, and they fit the All-Clad pans perfectly.

Sempre fui muito fã dos produtos da All-Clad. Sei de su excelente qualidade e durabilidade. Infelizmente o custo de importação é muito alto e impeditivo para ter uma coleção na cozinha. Entretanto, tive a sorte de ver a promoção da Amazon e cries a coragem de comprar. Valeu cada centavo gasto. Pena que nnao tem outras promoções com os demais produtos da All Clad. So como exemplo, um ovo sendo frito sem nenhum oleo, desliza na panela
Excelente producto. cambié mis sartenes de hace años por estos.
